post and rail (fence)
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a fence composed of posts and rails morticed together [often used in horse-grazing country.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:posts and rails
Pronunciation:
Notes: posts and rails		Also elsewhere; aka post and rails; note also posts and rails usually in reference to components of fence rather than the fence; includes attributive use
